#compdef mcp-nats
# ============================================================================
# mcp-nats - Model Context Protocol server for NATS (Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Goose (Gooseus)
# Upstream: https://github.com/Gooseus/mcp-nats
# npm    : mcp-nats
#
# mcp-nats is an MCP (Model Context Protocol) server that exposes
# NATS Core + JetStream + KV + Object Store + Consumer + Stream-
# health surfaces as MCP tools + resources, so LLM agents (Claude,
# GPT, etc.) can inspect, publish, subscribe, and operate a NATS
# cluster through the MCP protocol over stdio or SSE.
#
# The NATS client lane is built on `nats ^2.29.3` (declared verbatim
# at upstream package.json HEAD), the canonical Node NATS client
# by Synadia / nats-io (github.com/nats-io/nats.js, 400+ stars).
# The library implements the full NATS wire protocol: core pub/sub,
# request/reply with response queuing, NATS JetStream (consumers
# + streams + key-value + object stores), JetStream domains +
# accounts, nkeys + JWT credential model, and the new V2 KV / OS
# APIs. It is the dependency-of-record for every Node program
# that integrates with NATS - from Fastify backends to NestJS
# microservice transports to MCP servers like this one.
#
# Verbatim from upstream `src/connection.ts`:
#
#     import { connect, type NatsConnection } from "nats";
#     export async function createNatsConnection(): Promise<NatsConnection> {
#         return await connect({
#             servers: process.env.NATS_URL || "nats://localhost:4222",
#             user: process.env.NATS_USER,
#             pass: process.env.NATS_PASS,
#             token: process.env.NATS_TOKEN,
#             ...
#         });
#     }
#
# Then `tools/core.ts`, `tools/kv.ts`, `tools/jetstream.ts`,
# `tools/subscribe.ts`, `tools/consumers.ts`, `tools/objectstore.ts`
# wrap the connection methods as MCP tool handlers.
#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# AXIS 209 :: NATS MESSAGING PROTOCOL (CORE + JETSTREAM)  [CLOSES]
# Round 1327 :: TS-Node slot 3 of 4 :: CLOSES Axis 209 (202nd axis closed)
#
# Cross-language canonical library family for this axis:
#   Rust    : nats-io/nats.rs (async-nats)   [R1325 _rustfs]
#   Go      : nats-io/nats.go                [R1326 _ajc]
#   TS/Node : nats-io/nats.js                [R1327 THIS FILE]
#
# All three closers are first-party Synadia / nats-io clients with
# feature parity - core pub/sub, JetStream consumers + streams +
# KV + Object Store. The 2026 "LLM-agent shape" visible in this
# axis closure is structurally distinctive: the Rust opener
# (rustfs) is a production object store using NATS for event
# notifications, the Go middle (ajc) is a job-processing CLI for
# operators, and the Node closer (mcp-nats) is an LLM-agent
# integration that exposes NATS as MCP tools. The progression
# Rust(server) -> Go(operator-CLI) -> Node(agent-MCP) is the
# 2026 default cross-lane workload split.
# ============================================================================

_mcp-nats() {
    local context state state_descr line
    typeset -A opt_args

    _arguments -s -S \
        '--transport=[transport type]:transport:(stdio sse)' \
        '--port=[HTTP port for SSE transport (default 3000)]:port:' \
        '--host=[host to bind for SSE transport (default 0.0.0.0)]:host:' \
        '(- *)'{-h,--help}'[show help]'
}

_mcp-nats "$@"
